UML:TaggedValue.value: In addition to elements defined in the 19109 UML profile this package includes copies of re-used elements from the 19103 UML profile.
In addition to elements defined in the 19109 UML profile this package includes copies of re-used elements from the 19103 UML profile.
Point, Curve, Surface, Node Edge, Complex

A common mode of sampling is at a point. In environmental measurements and monitoring the term Station is often used. The class SF_SamplingPoint (Figure 10) is an instance of the «metaclass» GF_FeatureType (ISO 19109), which therefore represents a feature type. SF_SamplingPoint shall support one association.

Example values - acrisol - albeluvisol - alisol - andosol - anthrosol - arenosol ...
See http://www.fao.org/docrep/W8594E/w8594e0h.htm for the complete list of values

The operation evaluate shall accept a DirectPosition as input and return the record of attribute values for that direct position. The data type Record is defined in ISO 19103. If the direct position passed is not in the spatiotemporal domain, then an error message shall be generated

The operation "evaluateInverse" shall accept a Record of values as input and return a set of CV_DomainObjects. Normally, this will be the set of CV_DomainObjects in the Domain that are associated with values equal to those in the input Record. However, the operation may return other CV_DomainObjects derived from those in the Domain, as specified by the application schema.
